  "special": {
    "title": "It's a Madhouse! A MADHOUSE!!!",
    "description": "Shots sway left-right or up-down (chosen at random). On impact, each projectile splits into two, ricochets and gains speed with every bounce.\n\nRed text: It's a Madhouse! A MADHOUSE!!!\n\nBonus: +100% weapon damage, plus increased accuracy and magazine size."
  },
  "notes": "Fires poorly at distance but can blanket an area when aimed at the ground in the middle of a mob, especially in tight arenas.\n\nRicochets split at fixed angles, so Gaige's Close Enough tends to perform badly because the split rounds often veer past the target.\n\nShots are absorbed by ION Loader shields.\n\nBuzzard towers can be used as dependable banking surfaces to hit Buzzards.",
